The statutory registers are important. Not only is it a requirement of the Companies Act that they should be kept, and kept up to date, but the register of members, in particular, is the primary authority as to who are members of the company and how many shares they hold. Register of members (sec113 - sec128).he statutory registers are important. Not only is it a requirement of the Companies Act that they should be kept, and kept up to date, but the register of members, in particular, is the primary authority as to who are members of the company and how many shares they hold. Register of members (sec113 - sec128).
